qas.question: Jesus was known as the "King of Kings" because of his lieage from who?
Which name is given to Mary because of her role as a protector of captives?
Who was the mother of Jesus?
Which New Testament book provides a basis for the term Queen when referring to Mary?
What did David call Jesus when he met him?
What did David call Mary when he met her?
When Mary protected the captives of King David, what was she called?
When Mary assisted Kind David in finding his way to Jesus, what was the name given to her?
When Mary provided special counsel for Jesus, what name was she given?

context: Some titles have a Biblical basis, for instance the title <b5_0>Queen Mother<b5_0/> has been given to <a2_0>Mary<a2_0/> since she was the mother of Jesus, who was sometimes referred to as <b4_0>the "King of Kings"<b4_0/> due to his lineage of <a0_0>King David<a0_0/>. The biblical basis for the term Queen can be seen in the Gospel of <a3_0>Luke<a3_0/> 1:32 and the Book of Isaiah 9:6, and Queen Mother from 1 Kings 2:19-20 and Jeremiah 13:18-19. Other titles have arisen from reported miracles, special appeals or occasions for calling on Mary, e.g., <b8_0>Our Lady of Good Counsel<b8_0/>, <b7_0>Our Lady of Navigators<b7_0/> or <a1_0><b6_0>Our Lady of Ransom<b6_0/><a1_0/> who protects captives.
